LASSA FEVER - WEST AFRICA (31): NIGERIA
***************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Sun 3 Jun 2018
Source: Nigeria Centre for Disease Control [edited]
http://www.ncdc.gov.ng/diseases/sitreps/?cat=5&name=An percent20update percent20of percent20Lassa percent20feverpercent20outbreak percent20in percent20Nigeria


Highlights
- In the reporting Week 22 (28 May 28 - 3 Jun 2018) one new confirmed case was reported from Edo state.
- From 1 Jan to 3 Jun 2018, a total of 1982 suspected cases have been reported from 21 states. Of these, 432 were confirmed positive, 10 are probable, 1540 negative (not a case).
- Since the onset of the 2018 outbreak, there have been 108 deaths in confirmed cases and 10 in probable cases. The case fatality rate in confirmed cases is 25 per cent.
- 21 states have recorded at least one confirmed case across 71 local government areas (Edo, Ondo, Bauchi, Nasarawa, Ebonyi, Anambra, Benue, Kogi, Imo, Plateau, Lagos, Taraba, Delta, Osun, Rivers, FCT, Gombe, Ekiti, Kaduna, Abia and Adamawa); 17 states have exited the active phase of the outbreak while 4 - Edo, Ebonyi, Taraba and Adamawa states remain active - figure 1 [for figures, see source URL above].
- In the reporting week 22, no new healthcare worker was infected; 38 health care workers have been affected since the onset of the outbreak in 7 states - Ebonyi (16), Edo (13), Ondo (4), Kogi (2), Nasarawa (1), Taraba (1) and Abia (1) with nine deaths in Ebonyi (6), Kogi (1), Abia (1) and Ondo (1).
- Age group 21-40 years is predominantly affected (median age: 32 years) - figure 6.
- The male to female ratio for confirmed cases is 1.6:1.
- 81 per cent of all confirmed cases are from Edo (42 per cent), Ondo (24 per cent) and Ebonyi (15 per cent) states.
- One case is currently being managed at Irrua Specialist Teaching Hospital (ISTH) treatment Centre.
- A total of 5353 contacts have been identified from 21 states. Of these 55 (1.0 per cent) are currently being followed up, 5288 (98.8 per cent) have completed 21 days follow up while 10 (0.2 per cent) were lost follow up. A total of 84 symptomatic contacts have been identified, of which 29 (35 per cent) have tested positive from 5 states (Edo-13, Ondo-8, Ebonyi-3, Kogi -3 Bauchi-1 and Adamawa-1).
- National Lassa Fever After Action Review Meeting (AARM) scheduled for 5 to 7 Jun 2018.
- National intensive clinical workshop on diagnosis, management and control of Lassa fever in collaboration with ISTH North-east/North -west zones scheduled for 12 to 14 Jun 2018.
- Lassa fever multi-partner, multi-agency Technical Working Group (TWG) continues to coordinate response activities at all levels

